John Fegan (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Fegan_(actor) 0 John Joseph Fegan (19 July 1908 – 9 April 1981) was an Irish Australian film and television actor. He appeared in many Australian films and television shows in the 1950s, 1960s and 1970s, including the long-running series Homicide as Inspector Jack Connolly. He was born in Belfast, Ireland.
